etSessionsBranchRef` (`checkpoint/parse_tree.go:294`).\\n\\n### Step 3: Refactor `Write` to use `UpdateSubtree`\\n\\nReplace the flatten+rebuild pattern. Create blob objects for the 3 files, then call:\\n```\\nUpdateSubtree(repo, rootTreeHash, [\\\"<shard>\\\", \\\"<suffix>\\\"], [3 file entries], {ReplaceAll})\\n```\\n`UpdateSubtree` with 2-level path preserves sibling trails in the same shard automatically. `ReplaceAll` at the leaf replaces the trail's directory contents completely.\\n\\nExtract `buildTrailEntries(metadata, discussion, checkpoints) ([]object.TreeEntry, error)` helper for blob creation.\\n\\n### Step 4: Refactor `Delete` to use `UpdateSubtree` with `DeleteNames`\\n\\nCall `EnsureBranch()` first (fixes remote-only fallback issue), then:\\n```\\nUpdateSubtree(repo, rootTreeHash, [\\\"<shard>\\\"], nil, {MergeKeepExisting, DeleteNames: [\\\"<suffix>\\\"]})\\n```\\nAdd existence check by navigating tree at O(depth) before deleting.\\n\\n### Step 5: Add `ValidateID` to `Read`, `Delete`, `Update`, `AddCheckpoint`\\n\\nAdd `ValidateID(string(trailID))` guard at the top of each method. Uses existing `ValidateID` from `trail/trail.go:37` which checks for exactly 12 lowercase hex characters.\\n\\n### Step 6: Optimize `AddCheckpoint` to read/write only checkpoints file\\n\\nInstead of Read(3 files) + Write(3 files), navigate to the trail subtree, read only `checkpoints.json`, prepend the new ref, create a new blob, then splice back with:\\n```\\nUpdateSubtree(repo, rootTreeHash, [\\\"<shard>\\\", \\\"<suffix>\\\"], [{checkpoints.json blob}], {MergeKeepExisting})\\n```\\n`MergeKeepExisting` at the leaf level preserves `metadata.json` and `discussion.json` untouched.\\n\\n### Step 7: Remove dead code\\n\\nDelete `getBranchEntries` method (no longer called). Remove unused imports if any.\\n\\n### Step 8: Update `trail/store.go` — delegate `createCommit` to shared function\\n\\nReplace the trail store's `createCommit` method body with `checkpoint.CreateCommit(s.r