age\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01EoG9JN9vTjCk3NqugFNtpw\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Review 01 -- Code Reuse Opportunities in feat/trails\\n     2→\\n     3→> Status: pending-dev\\n     4→> Date: 2026-03-03\\n     5→> Reviewer: Code Review Agent\\n     6→> Verdict: REQUEST CHANGES\\n     7→\\n     8→## Scope\\n     9→\\n    10→This review is scoped to code reuse opportunities in the `feat/trails` branch diff against `main`. It covers six specific areas identified in the review request.\\n    11→\\n    12→---\\n    13→\\n    14→## Findings\\n    15→\\n    16→### 1. `trail.Store.createCommit` is a trivial wrapper around `checkpoint.CreateCommit`\\n    17→\\n    18→**File:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go:522-528`\\n    19→\\n    20→```go\\n    21→func (s *Store) createCommit(treeHash, parentHash plumbing.Hash, message, authorName, authorEmail string) (plumbing.Hash, error) {\\n    22→\\thash, err := checkpoint.CreateCommit(s.repo, treeHash, parentHash, message, authorName, authorEmail)\\n    23→\\tif err != nil {\\n    24→\\t\\treturn plumbing.ZeroHash, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to create commit: %w\\\", err)\\n    25→\\t}\\n    26→\\treturn hash, nil\\n    27→}\\n    28→```\\n    29→\\n    30→This method adds nothing beyond rewrapping the error with \\\"failed to create commit:\\\" -- the same message `checkpoint.CreateCommit` already uses internally. It is called in exactly one place: `EnsureBranch` (line 53). All other call sites (`Write`, `AddCheckpoint`, `Delete`) already call `checkpoint.CreateCommit` directly.\\n    31→\\n    32→**Recommendation:** Delete `createCommit` and call `checkpoint.CreateCommit` directly in `EnsureBranch`. This removes a misleading abstraction that suggests the trail store has its own commit logic.\\n    33→\\n    34→**Severity:** Suggestion\\n    35→\\n    36→---\\n    37→\\n    38→### 2. `verifyTrailExists` duplicates tree navigation from `readCheckpointsFromTree`\\n    39→\\n    40→**Files:**\\n    41→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go:460-482` (`verifyTrailExists`)\\n    42→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go:358-408` (`readCheckpointsFromTree`)\\n    43→\\n    44→Both methods perform the exact same three-step tree navigation: rootTree -> FindEntry(shard) -> TreeObject -> FindEntry(suffix) -> TreeObject. The first 20 lines of `readCheckpointsFromTree` (lines 360-383) are structurally identical to `verifyTrailExists` (lines 461-479).\\n    45→\\n    46→**Recommendation:** Extract a shared helper:\\n    47→\\n    48→```go\\n    49→func (s *Store) navigateToTrailTree(rootTreeHash plumbing.Hash, shard, suffix string) (*object.Tree, error) {\\n    50→\\trootTree, err := s.repo.TreeObject(rootTreeHash)\\n    51→\\tif err != nil {\\n    52→\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"trail %s%s not found\\\", shard, suffix)\\n    53→\\t}\\n    54→\\tshardEntry, err := rootTree.FindEntry(shard)\\n    55→\\tif err != nil {\\n    56→\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"trail %s%s not found\\\", shard, suffix)\\n    57→\\t}\\n    58→\\tshardTree, err := s.repo.TreeObject(shardEntry.Hash)\\n    59→\\tif err != nil {\\n    60→\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"trail %s%s not found\\\", shard, suffix)\\n    61→\\t}\\n    62→\\ttrailEntry, err := shardTree.FindEntry(suffix)\\n    63→\\tif err != nil {\\n    64→\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"trail %s%s not found\\\", shard, suffix)\\n    65→\\t}\\n    66→\\treturn s.repo.TreeObject(trailEntry.Hash)\\n    67→}\\n    68→```\\n    69→\\n    70→Then `verifyTrailExists` becomes `_, err := s.navigateToTrailTree(...)` and `readCheckpointsFromTree` uses it to get the trail tree and read `checkpointsFile` from it.\\n    71→\\n    72→**Severity:** Important (Should Fix) -- this is clear internal duplication within the same file.\\n    73→\\n    74→---\\n    75→\\n    76→### 3. `buildTrailEntries` blob creation loop -- no existing reusable pattern\\n    77→\\n    78→**File:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go:114-151`\\n    79→\\n    80→I searched the checkpoint package for a similar \\\"marshal-to-JSON, create blob, build tree entry\\\" loop. The checkpoint package's `WriteCommitted` does have similar blob creation calls, but they are interspersed with complex conditional logic (task checkpoints, chunking, multi-session metadata). There is no extracted helper for \\\"given a list of named JSON objects, produce `[]object.TreeEntry`.\\\"\\n    81→\\n    82→**Finding:** No existing utility to reuse. The `buildTrailEntries` helper is well-structured and cleanly factors out the repetitive marshal+blob+entry pattern. This is good new code.\\n    83→\\n    84→**Severity:** No action needed.\\n    85→\\n    86→---\\n    87→\\n    88→### 4. Commit + ref-update pattern is repeated 4 times in `store.go`\\n    89→\\n    90→**File:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go`\\n    91→\\n    92→The following 5-line pattern appears in `Write` (lines 99-109), `AddCheckpoint` (lines 343-353), `Delete` (lines 445-455), and `EnsureBranch` (lines 52-61):\\n    93→\\n    94→```go\\n    95→authorName, authorEmail := checkpoint.GetGitAuthorFromRepo(s.repo)\\n    96→commitMsg := fmt.Sprintf(...)\\n    97→newCommitHash, err := checkpoint.CreateCommit(s.repo, newTreeHash, commitHash, commitMsg, authorName, authorEmail)\\n    98→// error check\\n    99→newRef := plumbing.NewHashReference(plumbing.NewBranchReferenceName(paths.TrailsBranchName), newCommitHash)\\n   100→s.repo.Storer.SetReference(newRef)\\n   101→// error check\\n   102→```\\n   103→\\n   104→The same pattern also appears 4 times in `checkpoint/committed.go` for the metadata branch.\\n   105→\\n   106→**Recommendation:** Extract a `commitAndUpdateRef` helper on `Store`:\\n   107→\\n   108→```go\\n   109→func (s *Store) commitAndUpdateRef(treeHash, parentHash plumbing.Hash, message string) error {\\n   110→\\tauthorName, authorEmail := checkpoint.GetGitAuthorFromRepo(s.repo)\\n   111→\\tcommitHash, err := checkpoint.CreateCommit(s.repo, treeHash, parentHash, message, authorName, authorEmail)\\n   112→\\tif err != nil {\\n   113→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to create commit: %w\\\", err)\\n   114→\\t}\\n   115→\\tnewRef := plumbing.NewHashReference(plumbing.NewBranchReferenceName(paths.TrailsBranchName), commitHash)\\n   116→\\tif err := s.repo.Storer.SetReference(newRef); err != nil {\\n   117→\\t\\treturn fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to update branch reference: %w\\\", err)\\n   118→\\t}\\n   119→\\treturn nil\\n   120→}\\n   121→```\\n   122→\\n   123→This would reduce `Write`, `AddCheckpoint`, and `Delete` each by 8 lines and eliminate the repeated error messages. A similar helper could later be created in the checkpoint package, but that is a larger refactor outside this PR's scope.\\n   124→\\n   125→**Severity:** Important (Should Fix) -- four repetitions within a single 529-line file.\\n   126→\\n   127→---\\n   128→\\n   129→### 5. `trail.ID.Path()` and `trail.ID.ShardParts()` duplicate `checkpoint/id.CheckpointID.Path()`\\n   130→\\n   131→**Files:**\\n   132→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go:57-62` (`ID.Path()`)\\n   133→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go:66-71` (`ID.ShardParts()`)\\n   134→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/id/id.go:83-88` (`CheckpointID.Path()`)\\n   135→\\n   136→The `trail.ID` type is structurally identical to `checkpoint/id.CheckpointID`: same length (12 hex chars), same generation logic (6 random bytes), same regex validation, same `Path()` method (shard on first 2 chars). The `trail.ID` adds `ShardParts()` which `CheckpointID` lacks but could benefit from.\\n   137→\\n   138→The `GenerateID`, `ValidateID`, `String`, `IsEmpty`, and `Path` implementations are near-verbatim copies.\\n   139→\\n   140→**Recommendation:** Two options:\\n   141→\\n   142→(a) **Preferred:** Make `trail.ID` a type alias or embed `id.CheckpointID`. Since both are `type X string` with identical semantics, `trail.ID` could be `type ID = id.CheckpointID` or the trail package could define `type ID id.CheckpointID` and delegate methods. This eliminates ~40 lines of duplicated logic.\\n   143→\\n   144→(b) **Minimal:** At least add `ShardParts()` to `checkpoint/id.CheckpointID` (it is broadly useful) and note the duplication with a comment. `CheckpointID` does not currently have `ShardParts()` -- the checkpoint package uses `paths.CheckpointPath()` which returns the joined string. Having `ShardParts()` on `CheckpointID` would let the checkpoint package use `UpdateSubtree` more cleanly too.\\n   145→\\n   146→**Severity:** Important (Should Fix) -- structural duplication of an ID type with identical semantics.\\n   147→\\n   148→---\\n   149→\\n   150→### 6. `getBranchRef` and `getBranchTree` remote fallback -- duplicated pattern from checkpoint\\n   151→\\n   152→**Files:**\\n   153→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go:486-518` (`getBranchRef`, `getBranchTree`)\\n   154→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/committed.go:1331-1354` (`getSessionsBranchTree`)\\n   155→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/checkpoint/parse_tree.go:296-309` (`getSessionsBranchRef`)\\n   156→\\n   157→The pattern is: try local branch ref -> fall back to `origin/<branch>` remote tracking ref -> get commit -> get tree. This exact pattern appears in:\\n   158→\\n   159→1. `trail.Store.getBranchRef` (local `entire/trails` -> remote `origin/entire/trails`)\\n   160→2. `trail.Store.getBranchTree` (delegates to `getBranchRef`)\\n   161→3. `checkpoint.GitStore.getSessionsBranchTree` (local `entire/checkpoints/v1` -> remote `origin/entire/checkpoints/v1`)\\n   162→4. `checkpoint.GitStore.getSessionsBranchRef` (same, returns hashes only)\\n   163→\\n   164→The only difference is the branch name constant. All four follow the same structure.\\n   165→\\n   166→**Recommendation:** Extract a generic helper in the checkpoint package (since both trail and checkpoint import it):\\n   167→\\n   168→```go\\n   169→// ResolveBranchRef resolves a branch reference, falling back to origin/<branch> if local is missing.\\n   170→func ResolveBranchRef(repo *git.Repository, branchName string) (commitHash, treeHash plumbing.Hash, err error) {\\n   171→\\trefName := plumbing.NewBranchReferenceName(branchName)\\n   172→\\tref, err := repo.Reference(refName, true)\\n   173→\\tif err != nil {\\n   174→\\t\\tremoteRefName := plumbing.NewRemoteReferenceName(\\\"origin\\\", branchName)\\n   175→\\t\\tref, err = repo.Reference(remoteRefName, true)\\n   176→\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   177→\\t\\t\\treturn plumbing.ZeroHash, plumbing.ZeroHash, fmt.Errorf(\\\"branch %s not found: %w\\\", branchName, err)\\n   178→\\t\\t}\\n   179→\\t}\\n   180→\\tcommit, err := repo.CommitObject(ref.Hash())\\n   181→\\tif err != nil {\\n   182→\\t\\treturn plumbing.ZeroHash, plumbing.ZeroHash, fmt.Errorf(\\\"failed to get commit: %w\\\", err)\\n   183→\\t}\\n   184→\\treturn ref.Hash(), commit.TreeHash, nil\\n   185→}\\n   186→```\\n   187→\\n   188→Both `trail.Store` and `checkpoint.GitStore` can then delegate to this. The trail store's `getBranchRef` and `getBranchTree` collapse into one-liners.\\n   189→\\n   190→**Severity:** Suggestion -- the duplication is across packages and the abstraction is straightforward to introduce later.\\n   191→\\n   192→---\\n   193→\\n   194→## Additional Findings (Outside the Six Requested Items)\\n   195→\\n   196→### 7. `stripGitEnv` duplicated between `claudecode/generate.go` and `summarize/claude.go`\\n   197→\\n   198→**Files:**\\n   199→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/generate.go:64-72`\\n   200→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/summarize/claude.go:164-172`\\n   201→\\n   202→The comment on line 63 of `generate.go` acknowledges the duplication: \\\"Duplicated from summarize/claude.go -- simple filter not worth extracting to shared package.\\\" However, there are now two copies, and the `agent/claudecode` package is a natural home for agent-specific utilities. If a third copy appears, this should be extracted.\\n   203→\\n   204→**Severity:** Suggestion -- acknowledged duplication, monitor for a third occurrence.\\n   205→\\n   206→---\\n   207→\\n   208→### 8. `truncate` in `trail_cmd.go` vs `truncateForSummary` in `manual_commit_hooks.go` vs `stringutil.TruncateRunes`\\n   209→\\n   210→**Files:**\\n   211→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail_cmd.go:472-480` (`truncate`)\\n   212→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` (`truncateForSummary`)\\n   213→- `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/stringutil/stringutil.go:23-34` (`TruncateRunes`)\\n   214→\\n   215→There are now three truncation functions:\\n   216→- `truncate(s, maxLen)` -- byte-based truncation with \\\"...\\\"\\n   217→- `truncateForSummary(s, maxLen)` -- byte-based, first-line-only, with \\\"...\\\"\\n   218→- `stringutil.TruncateRunes(s, maxRunes, suffix)` -- rune-safe, configurable suffix\\n   219→\\n   220→The byte-based `truncate` in `trail_cmd.go` is not UTF-8 safe (it can split multi-byte characters). It should use `stringutil.TruncateRunes(s, maxLen, \\\"...\\\")` instead. Similarly, `truncateForSummary` could use `stringutil.TruncateRunes` after extracting the first line.\\n   221→\\n   222→**Severity:** Suggestion -- the existing `stringutil.TruncateRunes` is the correct tool for display truncation.\\n   223→\\n   224→---\\n   225→\\n   226→### 9. `containsString` and `removeString` in `trail_cmd.go` should use `slices` stdlib\\n   227→\\n   228→**File:** `/Users/soph/Work/entire/devenv/cli/cmd/entire/cli/trail_cmd.go:491-508`\\n   229→\\n   230→The codebase already uses `slices.Contains` in 8+ files (`claudecode/hooks.go`, `factoryaidroid/hooks.go`, `strategy/manual_commit_attribution.go`, etc.). The hand-rolled `containsString` and `removeString` functions should be replaced with:\\n   231→\\n   232→```go\\n   233→slices.Contains(m.Labels, l)                        // instead of containsString\\n   234→slices.DeleteFunc(m.Labels, func(v string) bool { return v == l })  // instead of removeString\\n   235→```\\n   236→\\n   237→**Severity:** Suggestion -- stdlib already in use throughout the codebase.\\n   238→\\n   239→---\\n   240→\\n   241→## Summary\\n   242→\\n   243→| # | Finding | Severity | Effort |\\n   244→|---|---------|----------|--------|\\n   245→| 1 | `createCommit` is a useless wrapper | Suggestion | 5 min |\\n   246→| 2 | `verifyTrailExists` duplicates `readCheckpointsFromTree` navigation | Important | 15 min |\\n   247→| 3 | `buildTrailEntries` -- no existing utility, well-structured | No action | -- |\\n   248→| 4 | Commit+ref-update pattern repeated 4 times | Important | 20 min |\\n   249→| 5 | `trail.ID` duplicates `checkpoint/id.CheckpointID` entirely | Important | 30 min |\\n   250→| 6 | Remote fallback pattern duplicated from checkpoint | Suggestion | 20 min |\\n   251→| 7 | `stripGitEnv` duplicated (acknowledged) | Suggestion | 10 min |\\n   252→| 8 | `truncate` not UTF-8 safe, existing `TruncateRunes` available | Suggestion | 10 min |\\n   253→| 9 | `containsString`/`removeString` should use `slices` stdlib | Suggestion | 5 min |\\n   254→\\n   255→**Overall assessment:** REQUEST CHANGES on items 2, 4, and 5 (clear duplication within the trail package and with the checkpoint ID type). Items 1, 6-9 are suggestions that improve quality but are not blocking.\\n   256→\\n   257→**Estimated effort to address all feedback:** 1-2 hours.\\n   258→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"7b547f27-ce75-4661-b420-5ce4cce6bc37\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-03T14:43:17.431Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"aec8496ef1f971a18\"},\"toolU